caer
====
AER event-based framework, written in C, targeting embedded systems.

INSTALL: 
- configure: 

$ cmake . 

one of the following option is required:
 -DDAVISFX2=1           ... set davisfx2 (for DAVIS240A/B/C models)
 -DDVS128_H=1           ... set dvs128 (for DVS128 model)

options: 
 -DJAER_COMPAT_FORMAT=1 ... cAER will use (older) file output format compatible with jAER
 -DENABLE_VISUALIZER=1  ... enable visualizer for calls of caerVisualizer()
 -DENABLE_NET_STREAM=1  ... enable tcp server for sending packets via network

- build:
$ make

- run: 
$./caer (see doc/ for more info on how to use cAER)

